reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very compact, decent quality brushes - good for travel
reviews.reviewText: PGRODE Travel Size Makeup Brushes Mini Set with Hard Case and Built-in MirrorI travel a lot, and always with just a carry on. These are a decent set of compact brushes. Not quite the quality of the ones I'll leave at home - but much more convenient.PROS:- Smaller brushes but still with nice handles that fit well in my hand- Very soft bristles- Nice case that doesn't waste any space, is compact - about 1" x 4" x 4". Latches securely.- Nice variety of brushes- Bristles are secured well - I tried to pull some out and couldn'tCONS:- Synthetic bristles.... but pretty soft considering they're not "real". I'm willing to live with an average quality brush in exchange for the convenience while I travel.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pretty good for the price
reviews.reviewText: For about $10 this is a decent take along brush set that can be good for travel or keeping in a purse.It's not super high quality, but at least some of the brushes worked well for me.The brush they say is for blush seems stiff and harder, I tried using it to apply a little bit of bronzer and it was ok for that, I didn't feel it was good for blush.The brush that is for loose powder actually worked best for me all around, I used it to apply blush.I tried both of the small eye shadow brushes. I used the fluffier one for my medium shadow that I apply over a wider area, I had to go back for more shadow twice as often as usual, and I didn't feel the coverage was as smooth as usual. The one they call a smudge brush I used to apply darker shadow in the corners of the lids. It was going on very light, I decided to dampen the brush, and then it worked a lot better. I generally use three brushes for eyeshadow, I needed one for the highlight on the browbone, I had to wipe off the fluffier brush and use that.The eyebrow brush worked really well, I use brown eyeshadow on my brows because my brows are not thick, and that usually works best, it was really easy to get good coverage with the brush and easy to use.This comes in a plastic case with a mirror built in ( I wish it had a magnifying mirror too, instead of the window). The lid and bottom aren't quite lined up correctly, so I have to push in the bottom a little in order to get the lid to click closed.I like the compact size, definitely takes less space than my usual brushes do.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super Soft in a convenient case!
reviews.reviewText: These makeup brushes are super soft with sturdy plastic handles. Five brushes to take care of all your makeup needs, powder foundation, powder blush, eye shadow, blending, and eyebrows. The bristles are very soft and stay in place after use. The brushes fit perfectly in a small plastic case that has a window on one side so you can remember what's in it and a small mirror on the other side. The case cover swivels open and close and closely tightly with a snap. This is perfect for travel or for sitting on your vanity in its pretty case. I recommend this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute And Good Quality/Soft Brushes/Top Case Part Was Uneven/Trouble Closing
reviews.reviewText: I decided to rate this travel brush set 4 stars. You get 5 small makeup brushes, a hard case for storage, and a built-in mirror. The brushes are nice and soft! I was actually impressed with the feel and quality. I have often come across travel size makeup brushes that are cheap. You also get a flat brush which feels nice and firm! The set is perfect for touch ups; it is great for long or short trips. The brushes are gentle on my skin and definitely get the job done. The only reason I removed a star was because the built-in mirror is positioned in an awkward way though I understand why this is the case. I also had slight trouble while closing the case because the top part is uneven. Overall, I would still recommend this product! The case and brushes are so cute. I will be getting more colors and tell my friends who travel too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect fit for your cosmetic bag
reviews.reviewText: This hard cased travel size makeup brush set is the perfect size to fit into your compact cosmetic bag or even your purse. The best thing is, every brush you need to do a full face makeover is included. This is great because you don’t have to buy each brush separately making the set a fabulous value. The brushes themselves are a nice quality. There’s no shedding, they are comfortable to hold and will work for a variety of applications. This is the perfect set for traveling or on-the-go, and I recommend considering it for either personal use or as a thoughtful gift idea.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars my go-to brush set when I'm out and about!
reviews.reviewText: The compact design and hard case with a built-in mirror make it incredibly convenient, especially when traveling. It has five brushes, each doing its thing – eyeshadow, powder, shadow, lip, and blush. They might be smaller than regular brushes, but they work just fine for me. The only thing is, if you're into heavy makeup, they might be a bit small. But for everyday use and travel touch-ups, this is nice! It's my go-to set when I'm out and about, and I'd recommend it to anyone who wants easy, on-the-go makeup.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a cute little travel brush set that you can take along anywhere. The square plastic case that holds the brushes doubles as a compact with a mirror inside. The case fits easily in a purse or makeup bag, and I like that the cases came in a variety of colors - the purple one suits me. There are 5 brushes: 2 large for blush/powder and foundation, and 3 smaller brushes for eyes or lips. That's enough to cover all the bases when I'm away from home. The brush heads are thick and the bristles don't fall out. It's a good quality kit and I'm finding it handy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for travel
reviews.reviewText: Pros:Hard case that can't accidentally openBrush bristles are softSmall mirror inside the caseCons:Case is hard to open and close - I have to squeeze the sides to get it to align to open and closeSome loose bristles in the brushes - fine after cleaningMinor imperfections in the handlesOverall this is a good basic set for travel. Not luxury by any means, but great for having a compact way to transport a set of brushes.
